<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Shed" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Shed,</orth> vb. (impf. and part. <emph>shed</emph>) 1) to let fall, to scatter, to cast: <cit><quote>the seeded pride must or now be cropped, or, --ing, breed a nursery of like evil,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.319" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 319</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to suffer or cause to flow out, to pour: <cit><quote>a bombard that would s. his liquor,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 22</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a wench that s. her milk,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.124" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 3, 124</bibl></cit>. Oftenest used of blood and tears; of blood: <bibl n="shak. ven 665" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 665</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.309" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 309</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.309" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 309</bibl> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.49" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.57" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.134" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.61" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 3, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.6.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 6, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.118" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 118</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.227" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 227</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.52" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.5.53" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 5, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.195" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 195</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.5.25" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.6.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 6, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.76" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 4.5.76" default="NO" valid="y